WEBVTT

00:01.435 --> 00:04.069
♪♪

00:04.071 --> 00:06.071
[ indistinct conversations ]

00:12.513 --> 00:15.481
Shut it down or get fired,
people!

00:15.483 --> 00:16.548
[ grunts ]

00:16.550 --> 00:18.017
Noah: All set?

00:18.019 --> 00:20.285
One sec.

00:20.287 --> 00:22.755
For over two decades, she's been
making sure I'm presentable.

00:22.757 --> 00:23.722
Where would I be
without her?

00:23.724 --> 00:25.591
Okay, we're ready.

00:25.593 --> 00:27.059
Man: Rolling.
Sound. Action.

00:27.061 --> 00:28.327
First question...

00:28.329 --> 00:31.764
Charlotte. Charlotte!
Charlotte!

00:31.766 --> 00:33.265
Who's in charge of the
president's detail today?

00:33.267 --> 00:34.400
His secret service detail?
Obviously.

00:34.402 --> 00:36.101
Call whoever's in charge.
Call them.

00:36.103 --> 00:38.337
Get them here now --
now, Charlotte, now!
[ pounding desk ]

00:38.339 --> 00:40.072
[ Abby sighs ]

00:40.074 --> 00:41.573
Thankfully, Noah,
we lean on each other.

00:41.575 --> 00:43.442
We lean on our marriage.

00:43.444 --> 00:45.644
But I don't know that you ever
get used to character attacks,

00:45.646 --> 00:48.047
Especially when they have
no basis in the truth.

00:48.049 --> 00:49.615
Part of the package
of public office.

00:49.617 --> 00:51.116
It's certainly
not new --

00:51.118 --> 00:53.085
Not that that makes it
any fairer to my family.

00:53.087 --> 00:54.186
Right.

01:02.530 --> 01:04.530
We're running it, people!

01:08.235 --> 01:10.536
Our marriage is stronger
than ever,

01:10.538 --> 01:12.504
But we're human, and it's hard
when they attack our friends.

01:12.506 --> 01:14.840
And Olivia has been
an important friend to us,

01:14.842 --> 01:16.475
As well as an advisor.

01:16.477 --> 01:18.177
Man: Crash box. North lawn.
Man #2: Sir, sir.

01:18.179 --> 01:19.144
I'm sorry.
You'll have to stop filming.
Ma'am.

01:19.146 --> 01:20.379
Crash box?

01:20.380 --> 01:21.613
An alarm, often tripped
by an intrusion.

01:21.615 --> 01:23.449
There's an intruder
in the white house?

01:23.451 --> 01:24.762
Falcon's secure.
Foxtail's secure.
Woman:
First lady's on the move.

01:24.763 --> 01:26.074
It could be a false
alarm, but we can never
take that chance.

01:26.075 --> 01:27.386
I'll be right back.
Please wait here.

01:27.388 --> 01:28.454
We're clear.
Foxtail's secure.

01:28.456 --> 01:30.089
[ indistinct conversations ]

01:30.091 --> 01:33.292
♪♪

01:33.294 --> 01:35.260
Fitz: Wait.
Protocol is the bunker.

01:35.262 --> 01:37.729
Why aren't we -- you said
there was an intruder.

01:37.731 --> 01:39.331
Abby: They lied.
I asked them to lie.

01:39.333 --> 01:40.883
I needed to get you
out of there, sir.

01:40.884 --> 01:42.434
What the hell
is going on here, Abby?

01:42.436 --> 01:43.869
[<i> indistinct shouting on tv</i> ]

01:43.871 --> 01:46.472
<i> Olivia pope, are you</i>
<i> the president's mistress?</i>

01:46.474 --> 01:47.806
[ chuckles ]

01:47.808 --> 01:50.109
<i> Yes.</i>

01:50.111 --> 01:51.510
[<i> shouting intensifies</i> ]

01:51.512 --> 01:53.112
"yes."

01:53.114 --> 01:54.179
"yes"?

01:54.181 --> 01:57.549
"yes"?!

01:57.551 --> 02:00.619
[<i> shouting continues</i> ]

02:09.296 --> 02:11.230
Noah.
So sorry about all of that.

02:11.232 --> 02:12.248
What'd you do,
pay a homeless guy

02:12.249 --> 02:13.265
To crash
the white house gates?

02:13.267 --> 02:14.633
The secret service
is handling

02:14.635 --> 02:16.268
What I'm sure was
a very real threat.

02:16.270 --> 02:17.436
Cut the crap, Abby.

02:17.438 --> 02:18.704
I'm gonna need that tape,
Noah.

02:18.706 --> 02:19.838
The tape
where the first couple

02:19.840 --> 02:21.206
Pledged their love
to each other

02:21.208 --> 02:22.675
At almost
the exact same time

02:22.676 --> 02:24.143
That Olivia pope confirmed
her affair with the president?

02:24.145 --> 02:27.613
People, the word of the day
is "silence."

02:27.615 --> 02:30.182
Not a peep, tweet, or whisper
leaves this white house

02:30.184 --> 02:31.683
Unless it has been approved
by me --

02:31.685 --> 02:34.586
No "off the record," nothing
"on background," not one slip.

02:37.658 --> 02:40.292
Our job is to protect
our president.

02:40.294 --> 02:42.794
Ohh.

02:42.796 --> 02:45.764
[ door closes ]
Mellie: Oh, look,

02:45.766 --> 02:48.367
It's the girl who can't shut
her legs -- or her mouth.

02:48.369 --> 02:49.935
We've got one hour
to give Noah baker

02:49.937 --> 02:51.703
An exclusive interview with
the president and first lady,

02:51.705 --> 02:53.906
Or he runs the footage of you
lying about the affair.

02:53.908 --> 02:56.241
What do you expect us
to say, exactly?

02:56.243 --> 02:57.910
The truth.

02:57.912 --> 02:59.378
The truth?

02:59.380 --> 03:00.546
The truth?!

03:00.548 --> 03:01.547
Yes, Mellie.

03:01.549 --> 03:02.748
We have no other choice.

03:02.750 --> 03:04.183
Thanks to<i> her.</i>

03:04.185 --> 03:05.684
We can spin this.

03:05.686 --> 03:08.353
Uh, you can say
you grew apart after...

03:08.355 --> 03:09.454
The death of your son.

03:09.456 --> 03:11.256
You can say
you're getting a divorce.

03:11.258 --> 03:12.624
You can say you're pained
by that, but, in the end,

03:12.626 --> 03:15.227
It's the best thing for
your family and the country.

03:15.229 --> 03:16.395
[ sighs ]

03:19.700 --> 03:21.934
Are you out of your minds?

03:21.936 --> 03:23.502
I am not saying
any of that.

03:23.504 --> 03:25.604
I am not sitting down with you
and Noah baker and --

03:25.606 --> 03:26.939
We cannot lie!

03:26.941 --> 03:29.308
We have no choice.

03:29.310 --> 03:32.244
Go to your office.
Wait there.

03:32.246 --> 03:35.747
We will inform you when
it's time to do the interview.

03:35.749 --> 03:38.984
[ scoffs ]

03:42.856 --> 03:44.656
[ Mellie sighs ]

03:47.861 --> 03:50.929
[ door opens, closes ]

03:55.236 --> 03:58.370
Before you settle
on the truth,

03:58.372 --> 04:00.405
There are other options
to consider --

04:00.407 --> 04:02.007
Less hazardous options.

04:02.009 --> 04:03.809
[ clears throat ]
we are fully aware.

04:03.811 --> 04:06.612
Door number two -- you cast me
as the trashy homewrecker

04:06.614 --> 04:08.947
With a long history
of seducing powerful men.

04:08.949 --> 04:10.949
We considered that.
And dismissed it.

04:10.951 --> 04:13.285
Door number three --
you admit the affair,

04:13.287 --> 04:14.786
But stay with Mellie
through your term.

04:14.788 --> 04:17.322
We are doing
the interview,

04:17.324 --> 04:19.458
Telling the truth,
and moving on...

04:19.460 --> 04:22.027
Together.

04:26.867 --> 04:29.601
I'll tell Noah
the interview's on.

04:33.874 --> 04:35.974
I'm sorry.
Stop.

04:35.976 --> 04:38.277
I should've warned you.
I wasn't thinking.

04:38.279 --> 04:39.378
I should've said --

04:39.380 --> 04:40.746
I loved what you said.

04:48.589 --> 04:50.289
[ chuckles ]

05:07.975 --> 05:11.710
[ indistinct conversations,
clock ticking ]

05:18.652 --> 05:19.618
Senator grant.

05:22.923 --> 05:25.757
Senator.
I know you're angry.

05:25.759 --> 05:27.059
I know this is difficult.

05:28.562 --> 05:31.496
I can't imagine what else
you must be feeling,

05:31.498 --> 05:34.733
But this interview is not
just to help<i> him,</i> senator.

05:34.735 --> 05:36.368
This interview
can work for you, too.

05:36.370 --> 05:39.604
[ sighs ] senator, please,
if you will just...

05:39.606 --> 05:41.540
Hi, there, red.

05:41.542 --> 05:43.542
Cyrus.
Why -- why are you here?

05:43.544 --> 05:44.910
I'm answering the call.

05:44.912 --> 05:46.378
Answering the call?

05:46.380 --> 05:47.846
Answering the call --
the call to serve.

05:47.848 --> 05:50.515
The call to serve?
Crap.

05:50.517 --> 05:52.417
I have been called into service
for my country, red.

05:52.419 --> 05:54.419
The junior senator of
the great state of Virginia

05:54.421 --> 05:56.421
Has asked me to serve
as her chief advisor.

05:56.423 --> 05:58.724
Ma'am, I am begging you,
for the good of the country --

05:58.726 --> 06:00.292
Now, now,
let's not do that.

06:00.294 --> 06:02.060
Stop and smell
the "'merica," red.

06:02.062 --> 06:03.795
Besides,
there's no time to beg.

06:03.797 --> 06:06.465
I hear there's a clock
ticking on an interview

06:06.467 --> 06:08.934
The president would like
the senator to participate in,

06:08.936 --> 06:10.369
And if that's the case,

06:10.371 --> 06:12.838
Well, then,
there are gonna be

06:12.840 --> 06:16.708
Some things we would like
in return.

06:16.710 --> 06:18.777
You are negotiating?

06:18.779 --> 06:19.778
Look at you,
quicker than ever.
[ sighs ] okay, fine.

06:19.780 --> 06:20.812
What do you want?

06:20.814 --> 06:21.513
We'll be in touch.

06:21.515 --> 06:22.914
What?

06:22.916 --> 06:24.416
Cyrus,
we are running out of time!

06:24.418 --> 06:26.918
So...Tell me.

06:26.920 --> 06:28.387
What do you want?

06:30.057 --> 06:34.025
I want to destroy
Olivia pope.

06:34.027 --> 06:37.162
[ voice breaking ] I want her
to suffer like I have suffered.

06:37.164 --> 06:39.498
I want her to suffer so much
it makes him suffer.

06:39.500 --> 06:41.133
I want to make them bleed.

06:41.135 --> 06:44.136
I want their every breath
to reek of poison!

06:44.138 --> 06:46.405
Mellie.

06:46.407 --> 06:49.074
This is a very
important moment.

06:49.076 --> 06:50.742
Don't waste it
being human.

06:50.744 --> 06:53.044
Your answer will define
your future.

06:53.046 --> 06:55.881
Think like a champion.

06:55.883 --> 06:57.549
Think like a warrior.

06:57.551 --> 06:58.817
[ pounds fist ]

06:58.819 --> 07:03.622
Raise your sword
and run into battle

07:03.624 --> 07:05.924
And tell me
what the inscription

07:05.926 --> 07:07.759
On your monument will read

07:07.761 --> 07:09.895
When the history books
glorify you.

07:11.632 --> 07:12.898
[ sighs ]
tell me.

07:15.803 --> 07:16.968
What do you want?

07:20.007 --> 07:22.140
I want the oval.

07:22.142 --> 07:23.575
Yes!

07:27.047 --> 07:28.079
[ camera shutter clicking ]

07:28.081 --> 07:30.482
There's been a hiccup.
Cyrus.

07:30.484 --> 07:32.050
Cyrus?

07:32.052 --> 07:33.585
Your wife
reached out to him.

07:33.587 --> 07:35.787
He's acting as her advocate
for the negotiations.

07:35.789 --> 07:37.522
[ chuckles ]
what negotiations?

07:37.524 --> 07:39.791
What they want in order to agree
to the interview.

07:39.793 --> 07:41.460
She'll get nothing,
and she'll like it.

07:41.462 --> 07:42.494
Sir!

07:42.496 --> 07:44.029
Get out of my way.

07:44.030 --> 07:45.563
This is a negotiation, sir,
not an argument.

07:45.566 --> 07:47.532
If you go in there hot,
we'll never make our deadline.

07:47.534 --> 07:50.769
Move!
Which is exactly why
you can't be involved.

07:50.771 --> 07:52.504
Excuse me?
It's too personal between you
and the first lady, sir.

07:52.506 --> 07:54.773
You don't know what the hell
you're talking about.

07:54.775 --> 07:56.575
Move now,
or you're fired.

08:01.682 --> 08:03.114
So fire me.

08:04.585 --> 08:05.183
Olivia: Fitz.

08:05.185 --> 08:07.586
Hear her out.

08:11.859 --> 08:14.259
I am doing my job, sir.

08:14.261 --> 08:16.561
I am focused on doing my job
for you --

08:16.563 --> 08:18.763
Protecting the oval,
protecting the presidency.

08:18.765 --> 08:22.667
May I ask, sir, what<i> you</i> are
focused on right now?

08:22.669 --> 08:25.270
She's right.

08:25.272 --> 08:27.105
Anger gets you nowhere.

08:30.544 --> 08:32.777
Nothing gets agreed on
without my say-so.

08:32.779 --> 08:34.112
Thank you, sir.

08:35.516 --> 08:37.582
[ sighs ]

08:37.584 --> 08:39.618
[ door closes ]

08:41.588 --> 08:43.088
[ sighs ]

08:43.090 --> 08:45.257
And the white house response
to pope's declaration

08:45.259 --> 08:47.592
Has so far been silence --
a total, complete lockdown.

08:47.594 --> 08:48.793
¿dónde está Olivia pope?

08:48.795 --> 08:50.095
¿está en la casa Blanca?

08:50.097 --> 08:52.097
Por ahora,
no sabemos, pero...

08:52.099 --> 08:53.665
[<i> camera shutters clicking</i> ]

08:53.667 --> 08:55.200
No, Olivia pope & associates
has no comment at this time.

08:55.202 --> 08:56.675
We're under attack.
[ phones ringing ]

08:56.676 --> 08:58.149
Hackers from all over
are trying to get in,

08:58.150 --> 08:59.623
But the firewalls are holding.
You're calling again, Jim?

08:59.624 --> 09:01.097
No comment means
no comment.

09:01.098 --> 09:02.571
No, I'm not answering that --
because...No comment!

09:02.576 --> 09:04.075
I see you stealth port scan,
Taiwan.

09:04.077 --> 09:04.876
Good luck getting past
the ips protocol!

09:04.878 --> 09:06.711
No inglés.

09:06.713 --> 09:08.246
Woman:<i> Once again,</i>
<i> if you have just joined us,</i>

09:08.248 --> 09:09.915
<i> Olivia pope has just --</i>
what are you doing?

09:09.917 --> 09:11.850
We were watching that.
Why? For what?

09:11.852 --> 09:13.852
Hey. Do you know
what you just did?

09:13.854 --> 09:15.153
I was in the middle

09:15.155 --> 09:15.987
Of delivering kill worms
to the power grid.

09:15.989 --> 09:17.155
Huck, holy...

09:17.157 --> 09:18.206
You were gonna turn off
the internet?

09:18.207 --> 09:19.256
Oh, no, I was gonna erase
the internet.

09:19.259 --> 09:20.292
Nice!

09:20.294 --> 09:22.727
No. No, not nice.

09:22.729 --> 09:23.828
Hey, we're helping Liv.

09:23.830 --> 09:25.096
Liv did not ask
for your help.

09:25.098 --> 09:26.131
She does not want
your help.

09:26.133 --> 09:27.599
She did this.

09:27.601 --> 09:28.867
You know why you don't know
about any plan?

09:28.869 --> 09:30.001
Because you are not part
of any plan.

09:30.003 --> 09:32.137
The plan already happened.

09:32.139 --> 09:34.272
The plan was Olivia pope
standing on that sidewalk

09:34.274 --> 09:36.741
And, with one word, obliterating
any life she's ever known.

09:36.743 --> 09:39.044
The plan was Liv requiring
the same thing of herself

09:39.046 --> 09:40.645
That she requires
of her clients,

09:40.647 --> 09:42.230
Standing by the one thing,

09:42.231 --> 09:43.814
Following the only rule
that matters to her.

09:43.817 --> 09:44.883
What is that?
Do not lie.

09:44.885 --> 09:46.718
Do. Not. Lie.

09:46.720 --> 09:48.186
That was it.

09:48.188 --> 09:50.255
That was her plan.
The plan is done.

09:50.257 --> 09:53.992
Liv finally stood on her own,
and we are done.

09:53.994 --> 09:55.260
So that's it?
No plan?

09:55.262 --> 09:57.862
We're just gonna sit here
and do nothing?

09:57.864 --> 09:59.264
My plan is to sit here

09:59.266 --> 10:02.167
And drink the majority
of this vodka

10:02.169 --> 10:05.937
And get remarkably wasted
and watch the world end.

10:05.939 --> 10:07.072
Anyone care to join me?

10:07.074 --> 10:08.740
[ crumpled paper lands softly ]

10:08.742 --> 10:11.176
In order to do
this interview,

10:11.178 --> 10:13.462
In which she will say

10:13.463 --> 10:15.747
That she and the president
are divorcing amicably,

10:15.749 --> 10:18.116
Senator grant requires
a few very simple things.

10:18.118 --> 10:19.884
First of all,
the president

10:19.886 --> 10:23.622
Will support the senator's bid
for the white house.

10:23.624 --> 10:25.890
That doesn't mean
waving a few pom-poms

10:25.892 --> 10:27.859
And phoning in
a couple of interviews

10:27.861 --> 10:29.761
On the Sunday circuit.

10:29.763 --> 10:32.697
It means that, politically,
the president is her bitch.

10:32.699 --> 10:35.100
He will be by her side
on the trail,

10:35.102 --> 10:37.235
At the click of
her ruby-red heels.

10:37.237 --> 10:39.070
He will fill
her collection plate

10:39.072 --> 10:40.739
As many times as she asks.
Got it?

10:40.741 --> 10:42.774
Is that it?

10:42.776 --> 10:44.776
Senator grant would also like
to limit the exposure

10:44.778 --> 10:46.177
Of this relationship.

10:46.179 --> 10:47.412
Olivia will not move
into the white house.

10:47.414 --> 10:49.381
Marriage is a nonstarter.

10:49.383 --> 10:52.250
The first affair doesn't make
any appearances

10:52.252 --> 10:53.718
As a public couple,

10:53.720 --> 10:55.253
Not until
senator Mellie grant

10:55.255 --> 10:57.288
Becomes<i> president</i>
Mellie grant.

10:57.290 --> 10:59.190
Additionally,
any and all interaction

10:59.192 --> 11:01.393
By Olivia pope
with the children --

11:01.395 --> 11:05.263
The senator's children --
must be cleared with her.

11:05.265 --> 11:08.133
I'll do my best.

11:08.135 --> 11:11.202
Before we become besties,
I have some demands of my own.

11:11.204 --> 11:13.038
I'm sorry.
<i> Your</i> demands?

11:13.040 --> 11:15.040
Namely that I refuse
to negotiate

11:15.042 --> 11:17.842
In this office and I refuse
to negotiate with you.

11:17.844 --> 11:22.013
Red, tell him what I said,
and tell me what he says back.

11:22.015 --> 11:23.381
Cyrus said Mellie wants you
on the trail --

11:23.383 --> 11:25.283
Campaign stops,
fundraising, photo ops,

11:25.285 --> 11:27.085
Whatever she thinks
she needs.

11:27.087 --> 11:28.987
That'll be more time than
we've spent together in years.

11:28.989 --> 11:33.158
She would also like the two
of you to remain discreet --

11:33.160 --> 11:34.959
No public appearances,
no photos.

11:34.961 --> 11:36.461
That's -- you tell Cyrus

11:36.463 --> 11:38.229
That what she's asking for
is out of the question.

11:38.231 --> 11:39.698
It<i> isn't</i>
out of the question.

11:39.700 --> 11:41.199
We need to be done
with her.

11:41.201 --> 11:43.134
We need to move on,
make a clean break.

11:43.136 --> 11:45.437
And this is how we do it --
by giving Mellie what she wants,

11:45.439 --> 11:47.405
By keeping her as happy
as we possibly can.

11:47.407 --> 11:48.973
We need Mellie
on our side.

11:48.975 --> 11:53.411
Fitz, I've negotiated
dozens of divorces,

11:53.413 --> 11:56.347
Amicable and ugly,
for husbands and wives.

11:56.349 --> 11:58.817
So believe me
when I tell you that,

11:58.819 --> 12:00.351
For 20 years of marriage,

12:00.353 --> 12:02.821
A few campaign stops
and a little discretion

12:02.823 --> 12:04.355
Isn't too much to ask.

12:04.357 --> 12:05.457
It really isn't.

12:05.459 --> 12:07.158
We need her to be happy,

12:07.160 --> 12:09.928
And that means letting her
feel like she's won.

12:13.100 --> 12:15.500
[ sighs ]

12:15.502 --> 12:17.736
Anything else?

12:17.738 --> 12:20.238
Cyrus says he wants to negotiate
with me and not Elizabeth.

12:20.240 --> 12:22.173
Why does that matter?
It's a power move.

12:22.175 --> 12:24.008
He's got an ax to grind
with Liz,

12:24.010 --> 12:25.510
And he's putting her
in her place,

12:25.512 --> 12:29.314
Not to mention driving a wedge
between Abby and me.

12:29.316 --> 12:31.049
A wedge?

12:36.323 --> 12:38.123
Abby.

12:38.125 --> 12:39.491
Why don't I let you two
discuss cyrus' offer?

12:39.493 --> 12:41.259
[ sighs ]
abby.

12:41.261 --> 12:43.094
[ sighs ]

12:43.096 --> 12:43.828
Abby.

12:43.830 --> 12:45.864
Hey.

12:45.866 --> 12:46.965
Is there
a problem here?

12:46.967 --> 12:48.233
A problem?
What kind of a problem?

12:48.235 --> 12:49.901
Like a friend who lied
to my face,

12:49.903 --> 12:50.835
That kind of a problem?

12:50.837 --> 12:51.970
Don't let cyrus turn this --

12:51.972 --> 12:53.371
No, this has nothing to do
with cyrus.

12:53.373 --> 12:54.873
You lied to me.

12:54.875 --> 12:56.040
I was trying
to protect you.

12:56.042 --> 12:57.186
You weren't trying
to protect me.

12:57.187 --> 12:58.331
I<i> was</i> trying to protect --
[ door closes ]

12:58.332 --> 12:59.476
You were trying
to protect yourself.

12:59.479 --> 13:01.262
Come on.

13:01.263 --> 13:03.046
You...Lied
right to my face.

13:03.049 --> 13:04.315
I asked you flat-out,

13:04.317 --> 13:05.483
And you said
you were<i> not</i> seeing him.

13:05.485 --> 13:07.252
You said, "no, abby,
i'm not sleeping

13:07.254 --> 13:08.520
With the president of
the united states,"

13:08.522 --> 13:10.488
To my face,

13:10.490 --> 13:13.158
And then i had to get up
on that podium

13:13.160 --> 13:15.860
And be humiliated in front
of all my peers.

13:15.862 --> 13:18.062
You left me
to die up there.

13:18.064 --> 13:19.330
If i had told you --

13:19.332 --> 13:21.266
If you had told me,
i could've protected you.

13:21.268 --> 13:22.751
If you had told me,

13:22.752 --> 13:24.235
I could've turned off the
cameras in the residence.

13:24.237 --> 13:25.837
If you had told me,
none of us

13:25.839 --> 13:27.272
Would be in this situation
right now.

13:27.274 --> 13:28.840
But you didn't.

13:28.842 --> 13:30.441
I didn't want you
to have to lie for me.

13:30.443 --> 13:32.844
I didn't want you to --
you didn't want to tell me

13:32.846 --> 13:34.579
Because you didn't think
i'd be good enough

13:34.581 --> 13:35.814
At my job to handle it.

13:35.816 --> 13:39.217
♪♪

13:41.087 --> 13:43.254
Did you?

13:46.059 --> 13:48.226
[ door opens, closes ]

13:55.268 --> 13:55.934
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

13:55.936 --> 13:57.168
I like martinis.

13:57.170 --> 13:59.103
[ laughs ]

13:59.105 --> 14:00.338
Oh, yeah, because james bond
likes them.

14:00.340 --> 14:02.907
It's -- hey, nothing to be
ashamed of, perkins.

14:02.909 --> 14:04.175
Every new spy does it.

14:04.177 --> 14:05.577
I did it.

14:05.579 --> 14:06.911
Me too.
[ cellphone ringing ]

14:06.913 --> 14:09.380
I got to take this.

14:14.054 --> 14:16.187
Olivia: Hey.

14:16.189 --> 14:17.255
How's it going?
[ door closes ]

14:17.257 --> 14:19.390
What's going on
over there?

14:19.392 --> 14:21.559
What's going on
over<i> there?</i>

14:21.561 --> 14:23.962
[ sighs ]

14:23.964 --> 14:26.497
I asked you first.

14:26.499 --> 14:29.234
Here, we're,
uh, drinking.

14:29.236 --> 14:32.637
Well, technically,
we're drunk.

14:32.639 --> 14:34.138
But, also, we're drinking.

14:34.140 --> 14:37.008
[ chuckles ]
sounds fun.

14:37.010 --> 14:39.911
I could use a drink.
[ sighs ]

14:44.284 --> 14:48.486
I think
i made a mistake.

14:48.488 --> 14:51.022
What i said
to the press --

14:51.024 --> 14:53.324
Not my best move.

14:53.326 --> 14:56.261
Just say the word, liv,
and i'm on my way.

14:56.263 --> 14:59.497
[ breathes deeply ]

14:59.499 --> 15:02.166
I'm good.

15:02.168 --> 15:04.602
Also,
you're too drunk to drive.

15:07.073 --> 15:09.440
Have one for me, okay?

15:09.442 --> 15:12.443
Done.

15:12.445 --> 15:15.079
[ cellphone beeps ]

15:15.081 --> 15:17.215
[ breathes deeply ]

15:20.487 --> 15:22.253
The president agrees
not to marry liv

15:22.255 --> 15:23.955
While in the white house.
Good. What else?

15:23.957 --> 15:25.690
And he will join mellie
on the campaign trail --

15:25.692 --> 15:27.025
Five stops max.
Eight.

15:27.027 --> 15:28.393
Six.
Seven.

15:28.395 --> 15:29.928
He won't go for it.
Then she won't accept it.

15:29.929 --> 15:31.462
Senator grant needs
president grant's support

15:31.464 --> 15:33.364
In order to become
the next president grant.

15:33.366 --> 15:34.632
Appearing at six
campaign stops

15:34.634 --> 15:36.501
Is better than none,
don't you think?

15:36.503 --> 15:38.369
Fine, six, but then mellie gets
the house in santa barbara, too.

15:38.371 --> 15:41.039
What? That house has been
in his family for generations.

15:41.041 --> 15:42.707
And olivia cannot take
the grant name.

15:42.709 --> 15:44.943
Under no circumstance can there
be a second mrs. Grant.

15:44.945 --> 15:46.477
We want that one
in writing.
Cyrus.

15:46.479 --> 15:50.014
Take the demands back
to the president,

15:50.016 --> 15:52.583
Or i will take them
to him myself.

15:52.585 --> 15:54.118
You're joking.

15:54.120 --> 15:55.320
And she wants it
in writing.

15:55.322 --> 15:57.422
What's next, my blood?
How about a kidney?

15:57.424 --> 15:59.157
Find out
which one she wants,

15:59.159 --> 16:01.025
And we'll cut it out
on national tv.

16:01.027 --> 16:02.026
This is total insanity.

16:02.028 --> 16:03.027
I'm just the messenger.

16:03.029 --> 16:04.295
Print up the agreement.

16:06.132 --> 16:07.165
Is that what you want,
sir?

16:07.167 --> 16:09.267
Let's get this over with.

16:11.604 --> 16:13.371
Tell me we have a deal.

16:13.372 --> 16:15.139
We have an agreement
if i can get it to print.

16:15.141 --> 16:16.741
[ printer beeps ]
toner?

16:16.743 --> 16:18.393
You've got
to be kidding me.

16:18.394 --> 16:20.044
Do you think the white house
was always her goal?

16:20.046 --> 16:21.546
Mellie?
I don't think so.

16:21.548 --> 16:23.314
Olivia. I mean, just looking
at her history...

16:23.316 --> 16:24.615
Well, she started small --

16:24.617 --> 16:26.751
Lobbyists, representatives,
senator davis.

16:26.753 --> 16:28.186
Do you think she broke off
that engagement

16:28.188 --> 16:29.554
[chuckling] 'cause she knew
she could do better?

16:29.556 --> 16:31.389
You've been digging
through cyrus' files.

16:31.391 --> 16:32.590
Just doing my homework.

16:32.592 --> 16:34.258
By reading the kill file
on olivia pope?

16:34.260 --> 16:35.410
[ sighs ]
you got to admit

16:35.411 --> 16:36.561
There's a pattern
to her relationships.

16:36.563 --> 16:38.463
We are printing out
these deal points.

16:38.465 --> 16:40.031
We are getting this
interview done.

16:40.033 --> 16:42.066
We are not gathering ammunition
against olivia.

16:42.068 --> 16:43.401
We already have it.

16:43.403 --> 16:45.336
Let's just hope
we don't have to use it.

16:45.338 --> 16:46.604
[ sighs ]

16:53.113 --> 16:55.546
[ sighs ]

17:00.220 --> 17:02.487
They caved on
the santa barbara house?

17:02.489 --> 17:04.756
They caved on everything.
Read the third page.

17:04.758 --> 17:06.758
I tacked on a maintenance
and staff allowance

17:06.760 --> 17:08.459
Of 500 grand a year --

17:08.461 --> 17:10.294
An allowance to be used
at your total discretion,

17:10.296 --> 17:11.362
I might add.

17:11.364 --> 17:14.799
[ breathes deeply ]

17:19.105 --> 17:20.538
[ breathes deeply ]

17:25.812 --> 17:27.445
No.

17:27.447 --> 17:30.314
What do you mean?

17:30.316 --> 17:32.617
I mean no.
I won't...

17:32.619 --> 17:34.452
I can't accept this.

17:34.454 --> 17:36.187
Mellie, we got it all.

17:36.189 --> 17:39.157
Fitz is giving you everything
you asked for.

17:39.159 --> 17:40.191
This isn't it.
This isn't enough.

17:40.193 --> 17:41.259
I should've asked
for more.

17:41.261 --> 17:43.327
More?
More.

17:43.329 --> 17:44.095
What more is there,
mellie?

17:44.097 --> 17:45.329
I don't know!

17:45.331 --> 17:48.299
I just know
that i want more!

17:48.301 --> 17:50.535
Well, what are you
gonna give them?

17:50.537 --> 17:52.470
In order to get,
you got to give.

17:52.472 --> 17:54.439
That's how this
whole thing works.

17:54.441 --> 17:56.207
It didn't used
to work that way,

17:56.209 --> 17:57.742
Not when<i> you</i> were
behind the wheel.

17:57.744 --> 17:58.643
You have lost it, cyrus.

17:58.645 --> 18:00.111
I've what?

18:00.113 --> 18:01.045
You have sat at home
too long

18:01.047 --> 18:02.747
With your tv
and your whore,

18:02.749 --> 18:04.382
And you have lost
your edge.

18:04.384 --> 18:08.719
The cyrus i knew
was an animal,

18:08.721 --> 18:11.756
A monster who cared about one
thing and one thing only --

18:11.758 --> 18:13.091
Getting it done.

18:13.093 --> 18:14.792
And<i> that</i> is...

18:14.794 --> 18:18.262
You're not him anymore.

18:18.264 --> 18:20.331
You don't have the fire.
You don't have the drive.

18:20.333 --> 18:23.234
You're soft.

18:25.705 --> 18:28.239
[ scoffs ]

18:29.843 --> 18:33.211
Everybody's changed on me.

18:36.616 --> 18:38.116
[ sniffs ]

18:38.118 --> 18:39.217
I'll see what i can do.

18:56.803 --> 18:59.270
[ door opens ]

18:59.272 --> 19:00.872
The president
will see you now.

19:03.776 --> 19:05.676
Cyrus: I know it's getting down
to the wire, sir,

19:05.678 --> 19:07.745
But at this point,
20 minutes out, i've done --

19:07.747 --> 19:11.282
I'm<i> doing</i> everything i can,
but mellie won't budge.

19:11.284 --> 19:14.819
[ breathes deeply ]

19:14.821 --> 19:18.556
I apologize that i haven't

19:18.558 --> 19:22.693
Been able to come through
for you, for the country.

19:22.695 --> 19:24.362
I'm sorry about that,

19:24.364 --> 19:26.664
But the senator's heels
are dug in, sir.

19:26.666 --> 19:28.299
She's...

19:29.369 --> 19:30.735
...Being mellie.

19:30.737 --> 19:32.537
[ breathes deeply ]

19:35.175 --> 19:36.941
You have been nothing
but gracious

19:36.943 --> 19:38.643
In these negotiations...

19:38.645 --> 19:40.344
And generous --

19:40.346 --> 19:42.747
More generous than i would be
if i were in your shoes.

19:42.749 --> 19:45.483
Unfortunately, mellie's not
operating on the same level.

19:45.485 --> 19:48.753
That's disappointing.

20:01.768 --> 20:03.968
What does she want?

20:06.506 --> 20:08.573
M-may --
may i speak frankly?

20:10.210 --> 20:11.943
[ breathes shakily ]

20:11.945 --> 20:14.278
I don't know if she'll ever
go for this.

20:14.280 --> 20:17.415
She's -- her feelings are hurt,
her pride, her heart.

20:17.417 --> 20:20.418
She may not have believed
you were in love,

20:20.420 --> 20:22.820
But...You liked her.

20:22.822 --> 20:25.556
Y-you were a team.

20:25.558 --> 20:30.428
And now -- now you took away
your friendship.

20:30.430 --> 20:33.431
Sh-she's bewildered.
She doesn't have anyone.

20:33.433 --> 20:35.866
She's lost, lonely.

20:37.937 --> 20:39.403
I don't know.

20:40.773 --> 20:43.474
I think...

20:43.476 --> 20:45.276
Go on.

20:45.278 --> 20:47.845
You need
to take her back.

20:47.847 --> 20:53.017
In my opinion,
that's how this goes away --

20:53.019 --> 20:56.721
If you take mellie back
and -- i'm sorry --

20:56.723 --> 20:59.423
Put your relationship with liv
on hold until you leave office,

20:59.425 --> 21:02.560
Until the spotlight shifts
from you to mellie.

21:02.562 --> 21:04.562
It's an unfair sacrifice,

21:04.564 --> 21:07.431
But one you may want
to consider,

21:07.433 --> 21:10.434
One that i'd advise you
to consider

21:10.436 --> 21:12.436
If i still worked
for you.

21:15.942 --> 21:17.875
Is that all?

21:17.877 --> 21:21.312
Yes, sir.

21:22.782 --> 21:24.282
Thank you, cyrus.

21:26.953 --> 21:30.488
Thank you,
mr. President.

21:44.437 --> 21:45.569
Where you going?

21:45.571 --> 21:47.371
I need some air.

21:48.608 --> 21:50.574
[ sighs ]

21:50.576 --> 21:51.676
Ugh.

21:51.678 --> 21:54.011
[ sighs ]

21:54.013 --> 21:55.680
I'm looking for my hooch.

21:55.682 --> 21:57.715
You didn't drink it --
did you, olivia? --

21:57.717 --> 22:00.084
While you were sleeping
in my bed like goldilocks?

22:00.086 --> 22:01.986
No.
[ sighs ]

22:01.988 --> 22:03.721
I hid it
all over back when...

22:03.723 --> 22:06.457
[ sighs ]
after the funeral.

22:06.459 --> 22:09.860
Now it's like
emergency supplies.

22:09.862 --> 22:11.529
I should go.

22:11.531 --> 22:12.730
[ chuckles ] you're gonna
need the hooch...

22:12.732 --> 22:14.532
[ sighs ]

22:14.534 --> 22:17.568
...All the hideously long days
and nights

22:17.570 --> 22:20.871
You're about to spend hosting
ridiculous galas and balls,

22:20.873 --> 22:22.640
Standing by his side,

22:22.642 --> 22:24.375
Your teeth
smeared with vaseline

22:24.377 --> 22:26.477
So your smile stays wide
and bright

22:26.479 --> 22:27.978
Like you're some kind
of wax figure.

22:27.980 --> 22:30.014
Ah! Yes!

22:30.016 --> 22:32.583
[ sighing ]

22:32.585 --> 22:34.719
Trust me,

22:34.721 --> 22:36.987
This stuff is the only thing
that gets you through --

22:36.989 --> 22:38.689
The lady lunching
and the curating,

22:38.691 --> 22:40.658
The tedious cause
you have to come up with

22:40.660 --> 22:42.393
And then pretend
to care about.

22:42.395 --> 22:43.894
Do you like to decorate,
olivia?

22:43.896 --> 22:46.597
Come wintertime, do you find
little snowflake ornaments

22:46.599 --> 22:48.632
And golden pinecones
just adorable?

22:48.634 --> 22:50.768
I hope you do because those
111 christmas trees

22:50.770 --> 22:53.104
Don't just
design themselves.

22:53.106 --> 22:55.873
[ sighs ]

22:55.875 --> 22:58.376
[ breathing heavily ]

23:02.448 --> 23:03.781
What the hell?
You want some?

23:07.954 --> 23:09.954
I didn't poison it.

23:09.956 --> 23:11.522
See?

23:11.524 --> 23:12.857
[ slurps ]

23:12.859 --> 23:14.725
Mmm!

23:14.727 --> 23:15.893
[ breathes shakily ]

23:15.895 --> 23:19.563
I don't want any.
Thanks.

23:21.601 --> 23:23.968
[ chuckles ]

23:23.970 --> 23:27.538
You don't get to say
what you don't want,

23:27.540 --> 23:28.639
Not in here.

23:31.043 --> 23:34.545
Your wants, your needs...

23:34.547 --> 23:38.149
Nobody cares anymore.

23:38.151 --> 23:41.786
All that matters
from now on is him.

23:41.788 --> 23:43.638
[ sighs ]

23:43.639 --> 23:45.489
You will make so many sacrifices
and compromises.

23:45.491 --> 23:46.791
[ chuckles ]

23:46.793 --> 23:49.827
You won't even feel like
a real person anymore.

23:49.829 --> 23:51.762
You will be unrecognizable.

23:51.764 --> 23:53.731
You think you're gonna be able
to keep that little business

23:53.733 --> 23:55.133
Of yours up and running,

23:55.134 --> 23:56.534
That group of thugs you got
working for you?

23:56.536 --> 23:58.102
What, you're gonna find
a place for them

23:58.104 --> 23:59.804
Here on your staff
in the white house?

23:59.806 --> 24:01.572
I don't think so.
You forfeit all that

24:01.574 --> 24:02.940
The moment
he takes your hand

24:02.942 --> 24:04.542
And presents you
to the world.

24:04.544 --> 24:06.544
You get dropped in a cage,
and you are trapped.

24:06.546 --> 24:10.981
The amount of bile you will
force yourself to choke down...

24:10.983 --> 24:12.550
[ breathes deeply ]

24:12.552 --> 24:15.119
But like i said,

24:15.121 --> 24:17.087
That's what this here
liquid gold is for.

24:17.089 --> 24:20.224
To feel numb.
Oh, honey, no.

24:20.226 --> 24:22.927
Living here
in this prison,

24:22.929 --> 24:26.063
That is what makes you
feel numb.

24:26.065 --> 24:28.866
This is what makes you
feel alive.

24:30.736 --> 24:33.737
[ breathes shakily ]

24:33.739 --> 24:37.141
[ sighs ]

24:39.579 --> 24:41.011
[ scoffs ]

24:41.013 --> 24:42.513
[ breathes deeply ]

24:42.515 --> 24:44.915
When you go back down
to the oval

24:44.917 --> 24:46.784
And you sit next
to fitz...

24:46.786 --> 24:48.886
[ sighs ]

24:48.888 --> 24:51.822
...I hope you know what
you're really fighting for.

24:51.824 --> 24:53.891
♪♪

24:55.895 --> 24:59.730
[ mellie laughs ]

24:59.732 --> 25:03.267
And whatever hooch you dig up
around here...

25:05.838 --> 25:08.706
...Consider it
my parting gift.

25:08.708 --> 25:11.242
♪♪

25:24.590 --> 25:26.057
Oh, abby!
You're good with words.

25:26.058 --> 25:27.525
Help me out with the lead
for my piece, all right?

25:27.527 --> 25:28.826
We open with the footage
of the secret service

25:28.828 --> 25:30.394
Busting through that door,
and it's chaotic,

25:30.395 --> 25:31.961
And they're like, "sir! Ma'am!
Defcon! Security!" whatever.

25:31.964 --> 25:33.898
I mean, people love that stuff,
right?
Uh-huh.

25:33.900 --> 25:35.099
And then my voiceover begins --

25:35.101 --> 25:36.867
"an intruder sent
the white house

25:36.869 --> 25:38.168
Into lockdown this morning

25:38.170 --> 25:40.037
And the staff scrambling
for cover.

25:40.039 --> 25:41.572
Turns out the only intruder

25:41.574 --> 25:43.240
Was ex-white house staffer
olivia pope."

25:43.242 --> 25:44.808
And then we cut
to the sound bite

25:44.810 --> 25:46.844
Where the president and
first lady blatantly lie

25:46.846 --> 25:48.612
And pretend that their marriage
is rock solid.

25:48.614 --> 25:49.847
I mean,
that is ratings gold, right?

25:49.849 --> 25:51.315
Maybe,
but you're not gonna need it.

25:51.317 --> 25:53.050
We are on track, noah.

25:53.051 --> 25:54.784
I promise you, you have nothing
to worry about.

25:54.787 --> 25:56.687
Okay, well, i'm just covering
my ass in case

25:56.689 --> 25:58.689
I don't see the first couple
in the next 16 minutes.

25:58.691 --> 26:00.291
I mean, you got
to be prepared, right?

26:09.936 --> 26:12.236
Abby:
[ muffled ] maybe if we offer
mellie a-a cabinet position.

26:12.238 --> 26:13.837
Fitz:
[ muffled ] absolutely not.

26:13.839 --> 26:15.072
An ambassadorship?
No.

26:15.074 --> 26:16.740
We're running out
of options, sir!

26:16.742 --> 26:18.175
Abby.

26:18.177 --> 26:19.910
Can you give us a minute?

26:19.912 --> 26:22.813
[ sighs ] fine.
But we only have 10 of them.

26:24.884 --> 26:27.685
[ door closes ]

26:29.221 --> 26:31.055
I'm calling it.

26:31.057 --> 26:33.290
You're what?
It's over.

26:33.292 --> 26:36.126
Mellie's...
Not taking the deal.

26:36.128 --> 26:38.062
Liv.

26:38.064 --> 26:39.296
Nothing we have to
offer is going to make
her change her mind,

26:39.298 --> 26:42.132
So...You take her back,
and we wait.

26:42.134 --> 26:43.701
Liv.
18 months.

26:43.703 --> 26:45.703
Is that how much longer
you have in office?

26:45.705 --> 26:47.271
Doesn't matter. What's the
difference at this point?

26:47.273 --> 26:49.239
Just take her back.

26:50.977 --> 26:52.643
She got to you.

26:56.015 --> 26:57.781
[ scoffs ]

26:57.783 --> 27:00.050
I saw her.
She talked. I listened.

27:00.052 --> 27:00.985
What did she say?

27:00.987 --> 27:02.019
It doesn't matter.

27:02.021 --> 27:03.621
It matters.
Why?

27:03.622 --> 27:05.222
Because i want to know what made
you decide to give up.

27:05.224 --> 27:06.357
I'm not giving up.

27:06.359 --> 27:07.358
You are giving up!

27:07.360 --> 27:09.727
On what?

27:09.729 --> 27:12.830
On you? On us?

27:12.832 --> 27:17.001
Or on everything i've worked
for my entire life?

27:17.003 --> 27:20.170
What exactly am i giving up
on here, fitz?

27:20.172 --> 27:23.340
There has to be something,
right?

27:23.342 --> 27:26.343
In order to be together,
in order to live here,

27:26.345 --> 27:30.347
In order to be
your first lady...

27:30.349 --> 27:33.851
You ever think about
what i'm giving up?

27:45.898 --> 27:48.732
[ sighs ]

27:48.734 --> 27:50.300
One of the valets
let me in.

27:50.302 --> 27:53.070
I'm not gonna say who because
they have two kids to feed

27:53.072 --> 27:55.205
And there aren't that many
valet jobs anymore,

27:55.207 --> 27:56.907
As far as i know.

27:56.909 --> 27:59.076
I just...

27:59.078 --> 28:02.046
Wanted one last moment alone
with this view.

28:04.216 --> 28:05.783
[ slurps ]

28:05.785 --> 28:09.687
[ sighs ]

28:09.689 --> 28:12.322
I'm sorry.

